<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10970</anchor> <rss>erct-001L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001L</addr>  <route>erct-001L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">sets</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001L.agda" type="external">erct-001L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10971</anchor> <rss>erct-003Q.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003Q</addr>  <route>erct-003Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001E.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001E" title="The truncation hierarchy">The truncation hierarchy</link> › closure properties</title> <parent>erct-001E</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10972</anchor> <rss>erct-001K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001K</addr>  <route>erct-001K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> types are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001K.agda" type="external">erct-001K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10973</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>As <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> with some centre <tex>a:A</tex>, we have for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> identifications <tex>\chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi _y \colon  a = y</tex>. Therefore, we identify <tex>x</tex> with <tex>y</tex> using <tex>\chi _x ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _y</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10974</anchor> <rss>erct-001L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001L</addr>  <route>erct-001L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">sets</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001L.agda" type="external">erct-001L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10975</anchor> <rss>erct-003X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003X</addr>  <route>erct-003X.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> identification types</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003X.agda" type="external">erct-003X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then for all <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10976</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The centre of contraction of <tex>x=y</tex> is given by our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>; the contracting identifications are obtained from the same assumption via <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10977</anchor> <rss>erct-003Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003Y</addr>  <route>erct-003Y.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> identification types</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link>, then for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10978</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>; the base case for <tex>n=-2</tex> is given by <ref addr="erct-003X" href="erct-003X.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>, and the other cases are trivial.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10979</anchor> <rss>erct-002T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002T</addr>  <route>erct-002T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type">Truncation</link> is upward closed</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002T.agda" type="external">erct-002T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>, then it is also <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10980</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, with two base cases given by <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10981</anchor> <rss>erct-002U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002U</addr>  <route>erct-002U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The identity map is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002U.agda" type="external">erct-002U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex>, the identity map <tex>1_{ A } \colon  A \to  A</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10982</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Immediate by identification induction.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10983</anchor> <rss>erct-002V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002V</addr>  <route>erct-002V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The identity map is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> for all <tex>n</tex></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002V.agda" type="external">erct-002V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex>, the identity map <tex>1_{ A } \colon  A \to  A</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> for all <tex>n</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10984</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We proceed by induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>: when <tex>n=-2</tex>, we recall that the <link href="erct-002U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002U" title="The identity map is contractible">identity map is contractible</link>, and in the inductive step we apply the <link href="erct-002T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002T" title="Truncation is upward closed">upward closure of <tex>n</tex>-truncation</link> to each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10985</anchor> <rss>erct-0026.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0026</addr>  <route>erct-0026.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0026.agda" type="external">erct-0026.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10986</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This can be seen using the cancellation laws of retractions.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10987</anchor> <rss>erct-0027.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0027</addr>  <route>erct-0027.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0027.agda" type="external">erct-0027.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>, then <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10988</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>s \colon  B  \to  A</tex> be a section of <tex>r \colon  A \to  B</tex>; if <tex>a_0</tex> is the centre of contraction of <tex>A</tex>, then the centre of contraction of <tex>B</tex> is given by <tex>ra_0</tex>. For the rest, we use <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10989</anchor> <rss>erct-003S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003S</addr>  <route>erct-003S.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of an <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> type is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10990</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>; the base cases for <tex>n=-2</tex> and <tex>n=-1</tex> are given by <ref addr="erct-002V" href="erct-002V.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> respectively. In the inductive step, we assume that <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> exhibits <tex>B</tex> as a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and that for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=_Ay</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> to show that for all <tex>u,v:B</tex> the identification type <tex>u=_Bv</tex> is likewise <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link>. The result follows from our assumption and the fact that <tex>u=_Bv</tex> is (by <ref addr="erct-003U" href="erct-003U.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>) a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>su=_Asv</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10991</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10992</anchor> <rss>erct-001J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001J</addr>  <route>erct-001J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sets</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001J.agda" type="external">erct-001J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called a <em><strong>set</strong></em> when for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10993</anchor> <rss>erct-0049.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0049</addr>  <route>erct-0049.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Propositional maps</link> are <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embeddings</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0049.agda" type="external">erct-0049.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional map</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10994</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-0049</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Fixing <tex>x,y:A</tex> we must show that <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x = y  \to  fx=fy</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>. By <ref addr="erct-002C" href="erct-002C.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-002D" href="erct-002D.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to exhibit a <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverse</link> to <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f }</tex> (it is convenient that the underlying maps of the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> need not be identical).</p>

 <p>We first define the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> <tex>s_{x,y} \colon  fx = fy  \to  x = y</tex>. Because <tex>f</tex> is assumed to be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>, we have by <ref addr="erct-001R" href="erct-001R.xml" taxon="Example"/> an assignment <tex>\phi _{x,y}:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} } \mathopen {} \left ( y,h ^{-1} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. We therefore define <tex>s_{x,y}h : \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( \phi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} .1</tex>; the witness of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sectionhood</link> can be constructed using <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \phi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} .2</tex> modulo some identification algebra.</p>

 <p>To construct the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> <tex>r_{x,y} \colon  fx=fy \to  x = y</tex>, we note by our assumption that we have an assignment <tex>\psi _{x,y}: \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}  =_{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} }  \mathopen {} \left ( y,h ^{-1} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, and we define <tex>r_{x,y}h : \equiv   \mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. It remains to show that for all <tex>x,y:A</tex> and <tex>h \colon  x =y</tex>, we have <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} =h</tex>. By induction on <tex>h</tex> it suffices to show that for all <tex>x:A</tex> we have <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,x} \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {refl}</tex>. We will deduce that <tex>\psi _{x,x} \mathsf {refl}  =  \mathsf {refl}</tex> from our assumption that <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link> and thus <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">fibred in sets</link> via <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10995</anchor> <rss>erct-003X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003X</addr>  <route>erct-003X.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> identification types</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003X.agda" type="external">erct-003X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then for all <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10996</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-003X</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The centre of contraction of <tex>x=y</tex> is given by our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>; the contracting identifications are obtained from the same assumption via <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10997</anchor> <rss>erct-002T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002T</addr>  <route>erct-002T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type">Truncation</link> is upward closed</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002T.agda" type="external">erct-002T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>, then it is also <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10998</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002T</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, with two base cases given by <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10999</anchor> <rss>erct-001N.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001N</addr>  <route>erct-001N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001N.agda" type="external">erct-001N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11000</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-001N</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <tex>a,a':A</tex> with <tex>\chi _ \bullet \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi '_ \bullet \colon \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a'=x</tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a, \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> with <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a', \chi '_ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, we employ the <link href="erct-0035.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0035" title="Covariant sum of an cocartesian family of path objects">covariant sum</link> of each of the <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001C" title="Dependent product of path objects">pointwise path object</link> structures on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x</tex> over the <link href="erct-0013.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0013" title="The intrinsic path object">intrinsic path object</link> structure on <tex>A</tex>, constructing an identification <tex>p \colon  a = a'</tex> followed by a homotopy <tex>H  \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}   \sim   \chi '_ \bullet</tex>. Fixing <tex>z \colon  A</tex>, we compute:</p>

  <tex display="block">      \begin {aligned}        \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}  z       &amp;=        \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{-=z}  \chi _z        \\        &amp;=        \chi _{a'} ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _z        \\        &amp;=  \chi '_z      \end {aligned}   </tex>

  <p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>, which we may deduce from <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11001</anchor> <rss>erct-001O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001O</addr>  <route>erct-001O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001O.agda" type="external">erct-001O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11002</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-001O</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>To identify two witnesses <tex>\phi , \phi '  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } x = y</tex> that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, it suffices via <ref addr="erct-0015" href="erct-0015.xml" taxon="Axiom"/> to exhibit a double homotopy in <tex>A</tex> identifying each <tex>\phi  xy</tex> with <tex>\phi 'xy</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, this follows from our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>